# Desktop and backend frozen

SpeedyCAT desktop v1 is complete and the Windows installer has been shipped. Treat **`anki/`** as read-only by default.

## Do not modify (unless the user explicitly requests)

- **`anki/`** in full: desktop Qt/Python UI, **`rslib/`**, **`pylib/`**, **`proto/`**, build/installer tooling under `anki/`, and related desktop-only assets.

## Still allowed

- **`Anki-Android/`** and other mobile-only work may continue to change.
- Workspace docs, Cursor rules, and **`Anki-Android/`** integration with the prebuilt backend AAR (until the user opts into a local backend build).

## Rationale

Avoid regressions in a validated desktop build; focus new work on mobile and ops unless the user reopens desktop or backend changes.
